\{\cos(x),\sin(x)\}
0\lt x \lt y \lt z \le \pi/4
\sin(x)\lt\sin(y)\lt\sin(z)\lt\cos(z)\lt\cos(y)\lt\cos(x)
A=\sin(x)+\cos(x)
B=\sin(y)+\cos(y)
C=\sin(z)+\cos(z)
A=B=C
f(t)=\sin(t)+\cos(t)
\frac{d^2f(t)}{dt^2}=-\sin(t)-\cos(t)<0
t \in (0,\pi/4)
B\gt \frac{A+C}{2}
